From: jlaiho@ichaos.nullnet.fi (Juha Laiho)
Subject: Need help w getgroups() (Bug?)
Date: Mon, 4 Oct 1993 17:35:59 GMT

Pray tell me why the following doesn't work:
#include <unistd.h>
#include <stdio.h>

int
main()
{
        printf("#groups: %d\n",getgroups(0,NULL));
        return 0;
}

To the best of my understanding (see unistd.h) this should print out the #
of concurrent groups for the current user, but it always prints out just 0.
